  "title": "Logistics Coordinator",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>You will coordinate logistics and warehouse operations for automotive accessories, ensuring accurate data processing, efficient order fulfillment, and smooth delivery. You will manage inventory levels, support sales, and address customer queries to maintain high service standards.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Liaise with operations and warehouse teams to process data accurately and update inventory systems promptly</li><li>Receive stock checklists and load items to the store using a trolley to maintain organized stock handling</li><li>Prioritize and allocate picking orders to courier companies to ensure timely export and local deliveries</li><li>Oversee store operations and manage inventory to maintain adequate stock levels of car accessories</li><li>Track product movement and forecast inventory needs based on sales trends to prevent stockouts</li><li>Maintain accurate stock records, monitor stock rotation, and manage replenishment activities</li><li>Process customer orders accurately and timely for both online and in-store sales</li><li>Coordinate preparation, packaging, and shipping of products to meet delivery schedules</li><li>Work with suppliers to ensure timely delivery of car accessories and resolve supply issues</li><li>Coordinate with shipping companies and logistics providers to track deliveries and resolve shipment delays or errors</li><li>Collaborate with the sales team to understand customer needs and ensure product availability</li><li>Address customer queries related to order status, shipping, and product availability promptly</li><li>Monitor returns and exchanges, ensuring compliance with store policies</li><li>Monitor and report on inventory levels and fulfillment rates to support operational decisions</li><li>Perform other warehouse administrative duties as assigned to support daily operations</li></ul><p>Skills:</p><ul><li>Use Microsoft Excel and Microsoft Office to update and maintain logistics and inventory data</li><li>Apply knowledge of automotive industry logistics and supply chain processes to support operations</li><li>Manage freight, shipping, and transportation coordination to ensure smooth product delivery</li><li>Execute packaging and store operations tasks to maintain product quality and readiness for shipment</li><li>Utilize warehousing and inventory management skills to optimize stock control and availability</li><li>Support sales activities by ensuring product availability and timely order fulfillment</li></ul>",
